Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning models for procedural content generation in games, which falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence and game development. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep convolutional networks and autoencoders for generating game content, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also covers the generation of game maps and levels, which falls under the graphics sub-category (cs.GR).
